  <title>tomboy-ng ToDo List</title>
  <text xml:space="preserve"><note-content version="0.1"><underline>tomboy-ng ToDo List</underline><size:small>

This is the tomboy-ng Known Issues and To-Do list for Github Wiki.  Its generated from a note in the tomboy-ng doc dir, don't edit the wiki directly.</size:small><size:huge>

<bold>Bugs and Feature Requests</bold></size:huge>

The correct place to discuss issues relating to tomboy-ng is the existing Tomboy mailings list. See  http://lists.beatniksoftware.com/listinfo.cgi/tomboy-list-beatniksoftware.com

Formal bug reports and feature requests should be via Github https://github.com/tomboy-notes/tomboy-ng/issues<size:huge>

<bold>Tested Platforms</bold></size:huge>

tomboy-ng is currently tested on a number of platforms , see https://github.com/tomboy-notes/tomboy-ng/wiki/System-Requirements

Reports of your experiences are very welcome ! <size:huge>

<bold>Known Issues</bold></size:huge><size:large><bold>

All Platforms</bold></size:large>
We don't do multilevel bullets.
Tabs do not work like real tabs should.<size:huge>

<bold>Here is a todo list (updated 2019/02/19)</bold></size:huge>

Recent fixes show as strikeout.

<list><list-item dir="ltr"><strikeout>Dark Theme works on Linux and, as much as is currently possible, on Windows.</strikeout></list-item></list><strikeout></strikeout>
<list><list-item dir="ltr">Embed images in a note. Technically something we can now do, indeed, some users have noted they can paste an image in there now but it does not last over a save / reload cycle. Images will break compatibility with old Tomboy and probably Tomdroid, so it will have to be optional. Will have to invent a means to save those images and, of course, work with the recover and archive models. Hmm....</list-item></list>
<list><list-item dir="ltr"> Stop house keeping from moving viewport.</list-item></list>
<list><list-item dir="ltr">Multilevel Bullets.</list-item></list>
<list><list-item dir="ltr">Restoring cursor position on note load.</list-item></list>
<list><list-item dir="ltr">Add <strikeout>menus to search window</strikeout> ?   Is this an alternative to splash screen  for RedHat users who have not installed Top Icons  and the approriate appindicator library ?</list-item></list>
<list><list-item dir="ltr">Network Sync</list-item></list>
<list><list-item dir="ltr">Links to other notes should be case insensitive. At present, the search is case insensitive, but the user's text is changed to whatever the other note's text actually is.</list-item></list>
<list><list-item dir="ltr"><strikeout>Sort out keyboard shortcuts and maybe even document ?  </strikeout>See help notes.</list-item></list>
<list><list-item dir="ltr">When user chooses to download the help notes in their own language (if available) its dependant on some OS issues. Won't work on Windows 7 and won't work on a Mac that does not have wget installed.</list-item></list><size:large>


<bold>Long term 'maybe' stuff</bold></size:large>
<list><list-item dir="ltr">Move notes into database (ie sqlite for small users, something bigger for BIG users). </list-item></list>
<list><list-item dir="ltr">Better export abilities - at present plain text, markdown and RTF. What about html, PDF etc ? Man Page</list-item></list>
<list><list-item dir="ltr">Import ability. Import a directory of Tomboy notes. Import other formats.</list-item></list>
<list><list-item dir="ltr">Revise controls, at present modeled on Tomboy, we can improve.</list-item></list>
<list><list-item dir="ltr">Install models - Flatpack, Snap etc ?.</list-item></list>











